{{- define "await-verdict-loop" -}}
- liza await-verdict — Block until review verdict arrives (call after submit-for-review; budget-aware)
  liza await-verdict {{.TaskID}} --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
  Blocks ~100s per call. Handle the response status:
  - POLL: call await-verdict again in the foreground, using returned timeout_seconds
  - REJECTED: read rejection reason, fix, resubmit
  - APPROVED, NEW_ATTEMPT, TIMEOUT, ABORTED: exit normally
  - Budget error: exit normally
  BUDGET: Call await-verdict at most 3 times. If no verdict after 3 calls, exit normally — the supervisor will restart you with the verdict.
  Do NOT poll liza get, cat /tmp, or any other command to check for verdict arrival between calls.
  Do NOT wrap in custom polling or background execution; await-verdict is the sole polling primitive.
{{- end -}}
